  <div
    class="m-auto bg-gradient-to-br from-big-stone-900 to-big-stone-950 py-2"
  >
    <HeadingTitle
      text="UHW's Latino Caucus Presents Donation Drive for LA Fires!"
      styling="m-auto font-Trebuchet font-bold text-center text-orange-400 py-5"
    />
    <div class="flex m-auto max-w-[90vw] lg:max-w-screen-lg">
      <CollageImage src={imgUHWDonation}>
        
      <div class="text-md text-white">
        <p class="py-2">
          In collaboration with UHW's Latino Caucus, we are collecting items
          to be distributed to <LinkText
            href="https://www.instagram.com/seiulatino">@seiulatino</LinkText
          > members in Southern California who have been affected by recent wildfire
          disasters.
        </p>
        <p class="py-2">
          Drop Off Locations: San Diego, Los Angeles, Fresno, San Jose,
          Stockton, Sacramento, and Oakland.
        <p>
        <p class="py-2">Drop Off Dates: January 15-17 & January 21-23</p>
          <p class="py-2">
            Weekend Drop Off: January 18-19 <b>(By appointment only)</b>
          </p>
          <p class="py-2">
            All items will be distributed to members and to the Antelope
            Valley YMCA who is supporting affected families in Altadena.
          </p>
          <p class="py-2">
            Scan QR code or click <LinkText
              href="https://www.amazon.com/hz/wishlist/ls/KT2AUCU794SW?ref_=wl_share"
              >here</LinkText
            > to find items needed.
          </p>
        </div>
      </CollageImage>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="py-2 bg-gradient-to-br from-honey-flower-200 to-honey-flower-300">
    <HeadingTitle text="Happy New Year 1107 Members!" />
    <div class="flex m-auto max-w-[90vw] lg:max-w-screen-lg">
      <CollageImage src={imgNewYear}>
        <div class="text-black font-Roboto">
          <p class="py-1.5">
            As we welcome the new year, we want to take a moment to appreciate
            the unwavering commitment of our union members to improving the
            lives of working people. Our members accomplished so much in 2024 -
            from historic contract wins, to electing labor champions across all
            levels of government, to uniting our communities and standing up for
            racial and social justice.
          </p>
          <p class="py-1.5">
            In 2025, we'll continue to advance a bold agenda that strengthens
            our union, our working conditions and uplifts the communities we
            live and serve. Join us for our 2025 SEIU 1107 Open House and Office
            Makeover Reveal! Check out our refreshed union office space and
            learn more about our 2024 victories and our plans for 2025!
          </p>
          <p class="font-bold py-1.5">
            Join us for our Open House & Office Makeover Reveal!
          </p>
          <p class="py-1.5 text-lg">
            Sign up for the <b>Virtual Event</b> via Mobilize below!
          </p>
          <div class="font-bold text-lg flex flex-col">
            <LinkText
              href="https://www.mobilize.us/seiunevada/event/747893/"
              target="_blank">Thursday, January 23rd from 3-7 PM</LinkText
            >
            <LinkText
              href="https://www.mobilize.us/seiunevada/event/747895/"
              target="_blank">Saturday, January 25th from 12-2 PM</LinkText
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </CollageImage>
    </div>
  </div>

  <main
    class="bg-gradient-to-br from-supernova-400 to-supernova-500 flex flex-col m-auto"
  >
    <HeadingTitle text="Together We Rise! Attend Our Membership Trainings!" />
    <div class="py-5 max-w-[90vw] md:max-w-screen-lg m-auto">
      <CollageImage src={imgTraining}>
        <p class="py-2 text-black text-xl font-bold text-left mx-2">
          The time to get involved is <i>NOW!</i>
        </p>
        <p class="text-md py-2">
          Join SEIU Local 1107 for a day of strategy and union power!
        </p>
        <p class="text-md py-2">
          We're coming together to share best practices for building a powerful
          labor movement and keeping our union strong.
        </p>
        <p class="text-md py-2">
          In order to keep our union strong - so that we can win better
          contracts, make breakthroughs in organizing, and build a more just and
          equitable society - we have to focus on improving our member strength
          like our very existence depends on it (because it does!).
        </p>
        <Button href="/membership_trainings" text="Attend A Training" />
      </CollageImage>
    </div>
  </main>

  <LatestNews
    bgColor="bg-gradient-to-b from-honey-flower-900 to-honey-flower-700"
    titleColor="text-supernova-400 shadowClass"
    textStyle="font-Roboto text-honey-flower-50"
    buttonStyle="bg-supernova-400 hover:bg-supernova-500 active:bg-supernova-600 text-honey-flower-800 hover:scale-125"
  />

  <StrongerTogether />
  <div class="py-4 bg-gradient-to-b from-honey-flower-900 to-honey-flower-700">
    <div
      class="tinyShadow py-2 font-bold font-Trebuchet text-center text-supernova-400 text-4xl md:text-5xl drop-shadow-2xl"
    >
      Why We're Joining Together
    </div>
    <div class="flex m-auto max-w-[90vw] lg:max-w-screen-lg">
      <CollageImage src={imgTogether}>
        <div class="text-xl text-white">
          <p class="py-2">
            Public service, home care and health care workers are joining
            together to get a real say over our wages, staffing, retirement, and
            working conditions. We're united, and we're building the strength
            necessary to secure record contracts, win policy changes in the
            state legislature and raise standards for all working people.
          </p>
          <p class="py-2 pb-5">
            We're standing up to protect the marginalized, fight for the quality
            services that Nevada residents and our patients deserve, and win
            fair pay increases for everyone—including chronically underpaid
            women and people of color—throughout our state.
          </p>
          <Button
            href="/join"
            text="Join Us"
            styling="mx-auto text-honey-flower-800 hover:scale-105 bg-supernova-400 hover:bg-supernova-500 active:bg-supernova-600"
          />
        </div>
      </CollageImage>
    </div>
  </div>

  <SocialMediaFeeds />
</Layout>

